\begin{definition*}
    {}
    A \emph{least fixed point} of~$f:\posA\to\posA$ is the minimum (if it exists) of the set of fixed points of~$f$:
    \begin{equation*}
        {}
        \lfp(f)\,\,\definedas\,\,\min_{\posleq}\,\{x\in\posA\colon f(x)=x\}.
    \end{equation*}
    \todotext{So if multiple minima exist, we say there is no least fixed point? If yes, perhaps say this explicitly, for clarity?}
    
    The equality in \cref{eq:lfp-one} can be relaxed to ``$\posleq$''.\end{definition*}
